== IBM definition ==
IBM[http://publib-b.boulder.ibm.com/Redbooks.nsf/RedbookAbstracts/tips0047.html?Open] defines '''Recovery Time Objective''' as the the time needed to recover from a disaster or, saying it another way, how long you can afford to be without your systems. 

== DRJ definition ==
DRJ[http://www.drj.com/glossary/drjglossary.html#r] defines '''Recovery Time Objective''' as the period of time within which systems, applications, or functions must be recovered after an outage (e.g. one business day). '''RTO'''s are often used as the basis for the development of recovery strategies, and as a determinant as to whether or not to implement the recovery strategies during a disaster situation.

== InformationWeek definition ==
InformationWeek[http://informationweek.com/story/showArticle.jhtml?articleID=164901978] defines '''Recovery Time Objective''' as the elapsed time from the occurrence of the disaster until business operations are restored 

== Greer definition ==
How long it takes to recover.

